VITALIS UGOH CALABAR – Arrangements have been con­cluded by the Etubom Council of the Obong Calabar to receive the Oba of Benin, His Royal Majesty, Omo N’Oba N’Edo, Uku Akpolokpolo, Ewuare II, and his traditional council. The three-day visit, de­scribed as “significant and historical will offer the two kingdoms to renew their long existing relationship and further discussions on how to sustain it.” Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Announcing the pro­gramme of activities to news­men in Calabar on Thursday, an Etubom in the Obong Council, Etubom Bassey Ndem, said the Oba and his en­tourage would arrive Calabar on Friday, January 10 through Monday, January 13, 2020. They would be hosted in Calabar by the Obong of Cal­abar, His Eminence, Edidem Ekpo Okon Abasi Otu V, Nat­ural Ruler and Treaty King of the Efik Kingdom. The Oba of Benin would be expected to pay a courte­sy call Governor Ben Ayade before departure. According to him, “the Oba of will be received in the grand reception at the Palace of the Obong of Cal­abar on Saturday 11, while on Sunday 12, January, there will be a royal banquet for him and his entourage.